<br>
Tips for keeping your weight down<br>
---------------------------------<br>
<br>
1) Buy muffins or grapes for food.  Both are dirt cheap and weigh only 0.1.<br>
<br>
2) If possible, have someone in your group &quot;master loot&quot; with autosplit off.  Instead, they can use the /split command when the group breaks up.<br>
<br>
3) See about others in your group ATMing.  Coin weighs 1 per 40 so monks can carry 599 coins if they have no other weight (like that could ever happen).<br>
<br>
4) Use sneak skill to trade with hostile or dubious merchants.  When sneaking behind such a merchant, you will consider it as indifferent.<br>
<br>
5) As a last ditch effort to control coin weight, buy and sell certain items with a merchant.  I think Amber may work well.  Buying something for 399SP 23CP and selling it back for 1PP 3GP will greatly reduce coin weight.  Considering most people will just destroy this coin, the loss is pretty insignificant.<br>
<br>
6) Buy summoned bandages and bags.  If you get disconnected, it all goes away, though.<br>
<br>
7) Lighter bags and 0.2 weight silk bandages go live in the next patch.  You may be able to get several of these from newbis tailors.  The benefit to a young monk is obvious.<br>
